\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 be placed at the center of a great many of them. It is through the telephone that many technologies work; it is thanks to the telephone that a vast numbers of social interac- tions and identity projects are shaped; it is again the telephone, including the smart- phone, that gives form to our everyday life. The telephone must then be reconsidered as a key-tool for contemporary societies. A new telephonic past can emerge and shed new light on past and present practices and metaphors. This issue is just a starting point of this emergence. 
